# API Route Conventions

## Structure
- Export named functions: `GET`, `POST` (not default exports)
- Add `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` for routes that must not be cached

## Security
- Rate limit every route using `rateLimit()` and `getClientIp()` from `src/lib/rate-limit.ts`
- AI routes: check `getServerSession(authOptions)`, return 401 if unauthenticated
- Never expose secrets or internal error details in responses

## Streaming (AI routes)
- Use `TransformStream` with `await writer.write()` for NDJSON streaming
- Set headers: `Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8`, `X-Accel-Buffering: no`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`
- Protocol: `{"type":"text","content":"..."}`, `{"type":"tool_start",...}`, `{"type":"tool_end",...}`, `{"type":"done"}`

## Error Responses
```typescript
return NextResponse.json({ error: "Description" }, { status: 4xx });
```
